The paper deals with a distributed consensus problem, which is a common topic in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The analysis of the 3-majority dynamics involves probability and information theory, which are relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also considers the presence of a malicious adversary, which is a security concern and falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
